JOHANNESBURG - At least 15 people were injured on Tuesday, when a taxi and car collided on the R23 outside Heidelberg in Gauteng, paramedics said. ER24 spokesperson, Ineke van Huyssteen, said that paramedics arrived on the scene just afterÂ 4pm, and found most of the patients outside of the taxi. "Upon further assessment, paramedics found a patient who sustained serious injuries. The patient was already being treated in the back of the provincial ambulance. ER24 transported five people who sustained minor injuries to hospital," van Huyssteen said. "The rest of the patients were transported to a hospital by various other medical services on the scene." Van Huyssteen said that the exact cause of the accident was unknown and would be investigated. African News Agency